trans-unit.source: Concerned about your BioAge? If you are concerned about your health or wellness, you should attend an appointment with a healthcare professional. BioAge is a new technology that many people will not have heard of yet, even in the medical community. If you want to discuss this report with a healthcare professional, we recommend you download the fact sheet to show them.
Now that you know your BioAge, what next?
We can improve our BioAge by taking small steps towards better health. Research tells us to focus on these three aspects of our health:

Your BioAge and your health are not done!
The following lifestyle recommendations have been proven tohelp people like you to optimize their blood sugar, weight and blood pressure.
Our advice on what you can do to improve your health:
Exercise helps the body use insulin more efficiently, which can lead to better blood sugar control. It can also lower blood pressure and help to achieve or maintain a healthy weight.
Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate-intensity exercise most days of the week.

Exercise helps the body use insulin more efficiently, which can lead to better blood sugar control. It can also lower blood pressure and help to achieve or maintain a healthy weight. Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate-intensity exercise most days of the week.

Eating a balanced diet that is rich in fiber, healthy fats, and lean proteins can help regulate blood sugar levels. Avoid foods high in sugar and refined carbohydrates, which can cause spikes in blood sugar levels.

Dehydration can cause blood sugar levels to rise, so it's important to stay hydrated by drinking plenty of water throughout the day. Drink plenty of water throughout the day to help curb hunger and promote good digestion.
Certain supplements, like chromium and magnesium, may help regulate blood sugar levels. Talk to your healthcare provider before starting any new supplement regimen.

Your BioAge and your health are not fixed!
Your next BioAge assessment is due in:
Every person has two ages: our chronological age (how old you are) and our biological age. Our biological age (or BioAge) is a measure of how well our cells, tissues and organs are aging.
Follow these health recommendations to stay on top of your BioAge
We detected a high level of exposure to smoke in your eyes.
Usually this result is due to being a current or previous smoker, or high secondhand smoke exposure.
Your smoking exposure is one (of many) contributors to your biological age calculation.
If your exposure to smoking is still high, it is recommended you reduce the exposure to improve your health and reduce your biological age gap.
Speak to your doctor for assistance.
What Makes our Technology so Unique?
When we look at your eye image, we can see features that contribute to the aging of your body. Our robust AI engine can see so much more.
Fundus image of a middle-aged individual with diabetes
Provides an estimate of your cardiovascular health.
Provides insight to your neurological health.
Helps estimate your rate of ageing and inflammatory health.
Provides insight to the rate at which your lens is ageing.
We use artificial intelligence (AI) which involves using super-computers to recognize patterns, classify, analyze and draw predictions from data.

The photo of your eye is passed through our AI engine which has learnt patterns from images from over 500,000 eye images (and still counting!) to recognize the various features of our eye health through photographs of your eye.
Analysis is performed at speeds beyond human capability, plus can recognize features a human may not be able to perceive.
